name: axios
text: President Trump falsely claimed in an interview with Fox News' Chris Wallace that the U.S. has the lowest coronavirus mortality rate in the world. https://t.co/bC8kH9onME

name: axios
text:
Trump asked press secretary Kayleigh McEnany to provide a chart showing he was correct.

The chart showed Brazil and South Korea have lower mortality rates than the U.S., but Trump still accused Wallace of being "fake news." https://t.co/bC8kH9onME

name: axios
text: Trump defended his opposition to removing Confederate symbols in an interview with Fox News, telling Chris Wallace that the flag does not offend him and that for many people it "represents the South." https://t.co/P0kMbFRTli

name: axios
text: Pressed on the fact that military leaders support renaming bases named for Confederate leaders, Trump responded: "I don't care what the military says. I'm supposed to make the decision." https://t.co/P0kMbFRTli
